               <p>JOSEPH BEAN. I live in Compton-mews, Bryanstone-square, and <rs id="t18311201-219-viclabel1170" type="occupation">drive a cab</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-219-victim1699 t18311201-219-viclabel1170"></join>. I was at the top of <placeName id="t18311201-219-crimeloc1171">Oxford-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18311201-219-crimeloc1171" type="placeName" value="Oxford-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18311201-219-crimeloc1171" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-219-off1168 t18311201-219-crimeloc1171"></join>, about eight o'clock in the evening, riding inside my cab, and saw my coat being drawn off the side seat; I saw the prisoner running away with it - I followed, and secured him with it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18311201-219-person1700">
                  HENRY 
                  GARNETT
               <interp inst="t18311201-219-person1700" type="surname" value="GARNETT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-219-person1700" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-219-person1700" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Policeman. I received the prisoner in charge; he said it was his first offence, and asked forgiveness - a woman threw the coat on his arm, and ran away.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>The prisoner put in a written Defence, stating that he had got up behind the cab to ride, when a man took the coat, and threw it on his shoulder.</p>
               <p>
